description.narrative: Countries have strengthened capacities to collect, analyse and use child-centered data and information, and to report on and monitor the situation of children, which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Adolescent Empowerment (Covid), Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Children With Disabilities, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, children in the Pacific benefit from an improved policy environment and evidence-based planning and financing.
